snippet.textDisplay:
You might not see or even read all of this, but if you do, please take it seriously.

Although I have heard of you before, I never watched your videos until this one and it’s awesome to see how far you’ve come. What I noticed the most about you is how sincere and genuine you are. Don’t let that part of yourself go.
Despite having great success as a content creator, it raised concerns to me when I saw how you used a ouija board at one point. Whether you believe it or not, contacting spirits through any of medium opens a spiritual doorway in your life and can be dangerous if you aren’t careful. For your own safety, I’d advise against doing anything like that in the future.

Now that you have nice things as a result of your success, understand that one day, all such things shall fade away just as all of us will. It’s great that you have these things - remember to stay humble and grateful. It is easy to get caught up in the midst of success. Yet the most important thing above all this is the question of “where will you go once you’ve passed away?” We plan for our future, but the truth is, tomorrow is not promised.

Jesus Christ is there for us and he has a place in His kingdom prepared for those who choose to follow Him. If you have any troubles/worries He is always there for you; know this because we will all encounter great trouble in our lives that will break us down to the point that we struggle to overcome our problems. Christ has overcome the world, even death itself, so if you stay by His side, you will have the hope and strength needed from Him in times of hardship. Most of all, He is the way to eternal life since He took our punishment and pain on the cross so that we, ourselves, would not have to suffer in eternal death. Through sin, we give way to ourselves to be separated from Christ, and therefore become spiritually unprotected, allowing other unclean spirits to enter into your body and have influence over your life. Since Heaven is a place without evil, pain, and sorrow, we cannot have spiritual evil inside of us if we want to be saved and make it into His kingdom.
Hell is a place that was made for Satan and all the fallen angels, not for us. Yet, countless of souls are condemned to that place everyday because they have made the mistake of going into sin, separating themselves from God, who does not want to send them there, nor takes any pleasure in doing so.
With all this in mind, please seek Jesus Christ with all your being, while there is still time left because once you have died, it is already too late. Do not get caught up in religion - the Word of God calls us to have a relationship with Christ and to live Holy, not just do things as a ritual or practice. Find out who Christ is for yourself and follow Him. He will never forsake you. I wish you all the best and may God bless you in Jesus Christ’s name, Amen.
